      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"meritocracy\" argument is a dangerous myth that conveniently ignores the starting line disparities baked into our society. It falsely presumes that everyone begins the race with the same resources, access to quality education, and inherited wealth, which is demonstrably untrue for people of color. Claiming \"equal opportunity\" is meaningless when the playing field itself is tilted by systemic racism and generational poverty. These arguments are simply ideological shields used to defend the existing, racially biased economic structure.",
      "source": "target",
